This paper proposes a method for generating clinical reports from raw recordings using natural language processing techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses image data (X-rays) and EEG data, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the user study and the interaction between doctors and the system, indicating that it could also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
